org.strongback.components

Interface Motor

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Requirable, SpeedController, SpeedSensor, Stoppable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    LimitedMotor, TalonController, TalonSRX

    @ThreadSafe
public interface Motor
extends SpeedSensor, SpeedController, Stoppable, Requirable
    A motor is a device that can be set to operate at a speed.

      • compose

        static Motor compose(Motor motor1,
                     Motor motor2)
        Create a new Motor instance that is actually composed of two other motors that will be controlled identically. This is useful when multiple motors are controlled in the same way, such as on one side of a TankDrive.
        Parameters:
        motor1 - the first motor, and the motor from which the speed is read; may not be null
        motor2 - the second motor; may not be null
        Returns:
        the composite motor; never null

      • compose

        static Motor compose(Motor motor1,
                     Motor motor2,
                     Motor motor3)
        Create a new Motor instance that is actually composed of three other motors that will be controlled identically. This is useful when multiple motors are controlled in the same way, such as on one side of a TankDrive.
        Parameters:
        motor1 - the first motor, and the motor from which the speed is read; may not be null
        motor2 - the second motor; may not be null
        motor3 - the third motor; may not be null
        Returns:
        the composite motor; never null

      • invert

        static Motor invert(Motor motor)
        Create a new Motor instance that inverts the speed sent to and read from another motor. This is useful on TankDrive, where all motors on one side are physically inverted compared to the motors on the other side.

        For example: 

           Motor left = ...
   Motor right = ...
   DriveTrain drive = TankDrive.create(left, Motor.invert(right));
        or 
           Motor leftFront = ...
   Motor leftRear = ...
   Motor rightFront = ...
   Motor rightRear = ...
   Motor left = Motor.compose(leftFront,leftRear);
   Motor right = Motor.compose(rightFront,rightRear);
   DriveTrain drive = TankDrive.create(left, Motor.invert(right));
        Parameters:
        motor - the motor to invert; may not be null
        Returns:
        the inverted motor; never null
